				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>There is a VERY SMALL SUBSET of the OOW augments which are usable in the new DON armor.&nbsp; While&nbsp;all OOW augments are slot 12, most are not usable in the VISIBLE armor slots.&nbsp; None of the flowstone ones can be used in visible slots for example, and only a subset of the&nbsp;-ite ones can.&nbsp; And the one's that CAN be used in this way are in demand because they are nice augments.&nbsp; Moreover, there isn't even a type 12 augment in the game that can go into legs!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This means that the vast majority of augments you're making as a rule aren't going into the type 12 slots on the armor.&nbsp; They are going into the type 7/8 slots.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So relax.&nbsp; The market will still be there.&nbsp; This is just a fix to allow us to actually use the type 12 slots for something when we make our gear. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
